CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 19, 1945, pg. 4 reads: "Popular Matron Buried - Widely known throughout the city, the popular Mattie Mills Jones (inset), who died suddenly here was buried from the Church of God, Paulson Avenue, recently. Mrs. Jones was the wife of Emmett Jones who was induated into the Armed Services just two days before she passed away.  Cain funeral establishment was in charge. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Women holding flowers, exiting Church of God, 309 Paulson Avenue, with other women lining sidewalks, for Mattie Mills Jones funeral
